    "Wu and Liu (2013) used pre-emphasis to reduce the Uyghur high-frequency signal by 6 db to improve the audio distribution.",
    "However, the dialect speech signal is not stable.",
    "Therefore, framing divides the continuous speech signal into short-term and equal-length segments.",
    "It aims to give short-time stationarity to the speech signal (Labied et al. 2022).",
    "Generally, in the framing process, add windowing operations to effectively avoid signal interruption due to spectral distortion."
